According to Shockley-Queisser (SQ) limit, energy loss of a device contains three parts, as shown in the following formula42:1Eloss=Eg−qVoc=(Eg−qVocSQ)+(qVocSQ−qVocrad)+(qVocrad−qVoc)=(Eg−qVocSQ)+qΔVocrad,belowgap+qΔVocnon-rad=ΔE1+ΔE2+ΔE3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${E}_{{{{{{\mathrm{loss}}}}}}}=	 \, {E}_{g}-q{V}_{oc}=({E}_{g}-q{V}_{oc}^{SQ})+(q{V}_{oc}^{SQ}-q{V}_{oc}^{{{{{{\mathrm{rad}}}}}}})+(q{V}_{oc}^{{{{{{\mathrm{rad}}}}}}}-q{V}_{oc})\\ =	 \, ({E}_{g}-q{V}_{oc}^{SQ})+q\Delta {V}_{oc}^{{{{{{\mathrm{rad}}}}}},{{{{{\mathrm{below}}}}}}\,{{{{{\mathrm{gap}}}}}}}+q\Delta {V}_{oc}^{{{{{{\mathrm{non-rad}}}}}}}=\Delta {E}_{1}+\Delta {E}_{2}+\Delta {E}_{3}$$\end{document}Where ΔE1 is the radiative loss above bandgap, ΔE2 is the radiative loss below bandgap, and ΔE3 is the nonradiative loss. By measuring the electroluminescence quantum efficiency (EQEEL) of a device, the nonradiative loss can be easily calculated through the following formula:2ΔE3=qΔVocnon-rad=−kTln(EQEEL)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
