				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\Delta {E}_{3}=q\Delta {V}_{oc}^{{{{{{\mathrm{non-rad}}}}}}}=-kTln(EQ{E}_{EL})$$\end{document}Where k is the Boltzmann constant, T is the temperature in Kelvin. Relevant characterizations to calculate the energy loss can be found in Fig. 3 and Supplementary Fig. 13, and the results of detailed energy losses of OPVs based on four blends were summarized in Table 2.Fig. 3Energy loss analysis.
